text.data-name: Best practices Tabs provide the user with a way of viewing a subset of the information in a given section of content. Tabs can be used to display alternate view of the same content or break up a long workflow or page of information into separate buckets.

tspan.tspan: Tabs provide the user with a way of viewing a subset of the information in a given section of content. Tabs can
be used to display alternate view of the same content or break up a long workflow or page of information into
separate buckets. Tab labels should generally be short and sweet - one to two words - and parallel in nature.
They can be used as a form of tertiary navigation when necessary.
